[4] Myanmar
Date: Wed 27 Feb 2019
Source: Xinhua [abridged, edited]
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2019-02/27/c_137854924.htm


The increasing measles outbreak has infected about 1300 people with one death across Myanmar as of mid-February this year [2019], an official from the Public Health Department told Xinhua on Wednesday [27 Feb 2019]. In early February [2019], a child under 5 years old died of encephalitis, a complication caused by the measles, in the Mandalay region.

The Yangon region accounted for about 50% of nationwide cases due to the lack of full immunization coverage in some townships, said Dr Aung Naing Oo, assistant director of the Central Extended Immunization Division under the Public Health Department. The outbreak is occurring mainly in the townships of Hlaingthayar, Shwepyithar, Dagon Seikkan, and South Dagon in Yangon.

The Ministry of Health and Sports is conducting a measles vaccination drive for children aged between 19 months and 15 years. About 1276 laboratory-confirmed cases of measles, a potentially serious infectious disease caused by the measles virus, were reported in Myanmar in the whole of 2018.

